==English==
===Noun===
'''PhyloCode'''
#a draft Code of formal [[nomenclature]] intended to allow naming [[phylogenetic]] groups, of all living things, rather than [[taxonomic]] groups ([[taxa]]).  Officially, such names are intended to supplement [[scientific name]]s rather than replace them.

===Usage Note===
Appears as both '''PhyloCode''' and '''the PhyloCode'''
===Quotations===
*'''2004'''  They want to replace it with a more rational scheme they call '''the PhyloCode''' &mdash; ''New Scientist,'' 11 Sep 2004, p.12

*'''2004'''  Given the hostile reception '''PhyloCode''' has received so far, they have a lot of convincing to do &mdash; ''New Scientist,'' 11 Sep 2004, p.13

